## Step 2: Implement Meta Tags with React Helmet

**Objective:** Add unique, optimized meta tags to all page types using `react-helmet-async` for dynamic meta tag management.

**Actions:**

1. Verify `react-helmet-async` is installed:
   - Check `package.json` for `react-helmet-async` dependency (should be v2.0.5)
   - If missing, run: `npm install react-helmet-async`
2. Configure HelmetProvider in `src/main.jsx`:
   - Import: `import { HelmetProvider } from 'react-helmet-async';`
   - Wrap the app with `<HelmetProvider>`:
   ```jsx
   <HelmetProvider>
     <CartProvider>
       <RouterProvider router={router} />
     </CartProvider>
   </HelmetProvider>
   ```
3. Create meta tag utility function `src/utils/metaTags.js`:
   - Function to generate page-specific meta tags
   - Enforce character limits: Title ≤60 characters, Description ≤155 characters
   - Include Open Graph tags for social sharing
   - Include Twitter Card tags
   - Base URL: `https://neera.store`
   - Example structure:
   ```js
   export function generateMetaTags({ 
     title, 
     description, 
     canonical, 
     image = 'https://neera.store/theme-image.png',
     type = 'website' 
   }) {
     return {
       title: title.substring(0, 60),
       description: description.substring(0, 155),
       canonical,
       og: {
         title: title.substring(0, 60),
         description: description.substring(0, 155),
         url: canonical,
         image,
         type
       },
       twitter: {
         card: 'summary_large_image',
         title: title.substring(0, 60),
         description: description.substring(0, 155),
         image
       }
     };
   }
   ```
