## Step 3: Implement Structured Data (Schema Markup)

**Objective:** Add JSON-LD structured data to enable rich search results and improve search engine understanding of content.

**Actions:**

1. Create schema markup utility `src/utils/schemaMarkup.js`:
   - Functions to generate JSON-LD for different schema types
   - Product schema for product pages
   - BreadcrumbList schema for navigation
   - Organization schema site-wide
   - CollectionPage schema for category pages
2. Implement Organization schema (site-wide):
   ```js
   export function getOrganizationSchema() {
     return {
       "@context": "https://schema.org",
       "@type": "Organization",
       "name": "Neera Sarees",
       "url": "https://neera.store",
       "logo": "https://neera.store/Neera logo.png",
       "description": "Premium handwoven sarees with authentic craftsmanship",
       "sameAs": [
         // Add social media links if available
       ]
     };
   }
   ```
3. Implement Product schema for product pages:
   ```js
   export function getProductSchema(product) {
     return {
       "@context": "https://schema.org",
       "@type": "Product",
       "name": product.name,
       "image": product.images,
       "description": `${product.fabric_type} saree, ${product.print_type}`,
       "sku": product.id.toString(),
       "brand": {
         "@type": "Brand",
         "name": "Neera Sarees"
       },
       "offers": {
         "@type": "Offer",
         "url": `https://neera.store/products/${product.fabric_type}/${product.slug}`,
         "priceCurrency": "INR",
         "price": product.selling_price || product.mrp,
         "availability": product.in_stock ? "https://schema.org/InStock" : "https://schema.org/OutOfStock",
         "priceValidUntil": new Date(Date.now() + 365*24*60*60*1000).toISOString().split('T')[0]
       }
     };
   }
   ```
4. Implement BreadcrumbList schema:
   ```js
   export function getBreadcrumbSchema(breadcrumbs) {
     return {
       "@context": "https://schema.org",
       "@type": "BreadcrumbList",
       "itemListElement": breadcrumbs.map((crumb, index) => ({
         "@type": "ListItem",
         "position": index + 1,
         "name": crumb.name,
         "item": `https://neera.store${crumb.path}`
       }))
     };
   }
   ```
5. Implement CollectionPage schema for category pages:
   ```js
   export function getCollectionSchema(name, description, url, numItems) {
     return {
       "@context": "https://schema.org",
       "@type": "CollectionPage",
       "name": name,
       "description": description,
       "url": url,
       "numberOfItems": numItems
     };
   }
   ```
6. Add schema to Helmet in Product pages:
   ```jsx
   <Helmet>
     {/* Meta tags */}
     <script type="application/ld+json">
       {JSON.stringify(getProductSchema(product))}
     </script>
     <script type="application/ld+json">
       {JSON.stringify(getOrganizationSchema())}
     </script>
   </Helmet>
   ```
7. Add schema to All Sarees page:
   ```jsx
   <Helmet>
     {/* Meta tags */}
     <script type="application/ld+json">
       {JSON.stringify(getCollectionSchema(
         "Premium Handwoven Sarees Collection",
         "Discover 137+ authentic handwoven sarees",
         "https://neera.store/products",
         filteredProducts.length
       ))}
     </script>
     <script type="application/ld+json">
       {JSON.stringify(getOrganizationSchema())}
     </script>
   </Helmet>
   ```
8. Add schema to Category pages (Fabric and Print):
   - Similar CollectionPage schema with category-specific data
9. Test schema markup:
   - Navigate to product page
   - View page source
   - Verify `<script type="application/ld+json">` tags present
   - Copy JSON-LD content
   - Validate using Google Rich Results Test: https://search.google.com/test/rich-results
   - Test 2-3 product pages, All Sarees page, 1 category page
   - Document validation results
10. Document implementation in PROGRESS.md:
