## Step 4: Optimize Content Structure & Semantic HTML

**Objective:** Improve heading hierarchy, semantic HTML tags, and content structure for better SEO and accessibility—without any visual changes.

**Actions:**

1. Audit current heading structure:
   - Navigate to All Sarees page in dev server
   - Open DevTools → Elements tab
   - Search for `<h1`, `<h2`, `<h3` tags
   - Document current hierarchy: "Current: [description]"
2. Implement proper heading hierarchy on All Sarees page:
   - Ensure exactly ONE `<h1>` tag exists
   - Recommended: `<h1>Premium Handwoven Sarees Collection</h1>`
   - Add visually hidden class if H1 should not be visible:
   ```jsx
   <h1 className="sr-only">Premium Handwoven Sarees Collection</h1>
   ```
   - Add to CSS if needed:
   ```css
   .sr-only {
     position: absolute;
     width: 1px;
     height: 1px;
     padding: 0;
     margin: -1px;
     overflow: hidden;
     clip: rect(0, 0, 0, 0);
     white-space: nowrap;
     border-width: 0;
   }
   ```
   - Use `<h2>` for section headings if applicable (e.g., "Filter by Fabric", "Sort by")
3. Implement heading hierarchy on Product pages:
   - Ensure product name is in `<h1>` tag
   - Example: `<h1>{product.name}</h1>`
   - Use `<h2>` for sections like "Description", "Details", "Related Products"
   - Verify no skipped heading levels (e.g., H1 → H3 without H2)
4. Implement heading hierarchy on Category pages:
   - Fabric page: `<h1>{fabricType} Sarees</h1>`
   - Print page: `<h1>{printType} Sarees</h1>`
   - Use H2 for subsections if needed
5. Replace generic `<div>` tags with semantic HTML where appropriate:
   - Navbar: Ensure wrapped in `<nav>` tag or has `role="navigation"`
   - Main content area: Wrap in `<main>` tag or `role="main"`
   - Product grid/list: Consider `<section>` with proper heading
   - Individual products: Consider `<article>` tags if appropriate
   - Example transformation:
   ```jsx
   // Before:
   <div className="container">
     <div className="product-grid">...</div>
   </div>
   
   // After:
   <main className="container">
     <section className="product-grid" aria-label="Product Collection">...</section>
   </main>
   ```
6. Add ARIA landmarks where semantic HTML isn't used:
   - If navbar isn't `<nav>`, add `role="navigation"`
   - If main content isn't `<main>`, add `role="main"`
   - Add `aria-label` to sections for better accessibility
7. Test that NO visual changes occurred:
   - Compare pages before and after modifications
   - Check spacing, fonts, colors, layout
   - Verify only HTML structure changed, not CSS/styling
8. Run Lighthouse accessibility audit:
   - Check if accessibility score improved
   - Document any new issues or improvements
